#PerfectPlanet takeover by @dolphindronedom

“The first clip features a humpback whale rising from the middle of a baitball in absolutely perfect conditions! This whale's name is Snowflake. Snowflake is a very special whale to me as it is the first humpback whale I ever saw breach, and the first whale that ever ‘mugged’ me…

“In the whale watching world, ‘mugging’ refers to the moment a whale sticks its head out of the water, making eye contact. Snowflake seemed to recognise our voices. It was a beautiful and life changing moment.”

A Perfect Planet tells the story of Earth's power and fragility. Oceans are the largest ecosystem on Earth, covering two thirds of our world’s surface and providing half the oxygen in our atmosphere. They’re home to as much as 80% of all life on earth, and nearly three billion people rely on them for their primary source of food.⁣⁣

For more about A Perfect Planet and where to watch, click the link in our bio.⁣⁣

Zooming to the moon 🌑
 
52 years ago today, the world bore witness to the first ever successful moon landing mission: the Apollo 11. The powerful Saturn V rocket carried Neil Armstrong, Buzz Aldrin and Michael Collins into space, where Armstrong and Aldrin descended onto the moon. Here they collected samples, took photographs, and conducted scientific experiments.

node.text:
When your restaurant order is no longer available 🥺⁣
⁣
Also known as the 'rock eagle-owl' or 'bengal eagle owl', the Indian eagle owl (Bubo bengalensis) can be found on the Indian subcontinent. Example prey may include rats, mice or even birds equivalent in size to a peafowl. One tactic they use to confuse predators when fending for their young, is to feign a wing injury, or fly in a zigzag direction. ⁣
⁣

Gliding... 😎 ⁣
⁣
There are two species of manta ray, giant manta rays (Mobula birostris) and reef manta rays (Mobula alfredi). As the name might suggest, giant manta rays are distinguishable by their generally bigger size. Amazingly, their wingspan can reach up to 29 feet wide!⁣

Hitching a ride 🐦⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The great crested grebe (Podiceps cristatus) is a diving waterbird residing in aquatic habitats such as lakes and reservoirs. Flamboyant courting behaviours during the spring include an extraordinary 'weed dance' where both birds carry water weeds in their bills and paddle ferociously, trying to maintain upright. This ritual is seen to be a display of stamina.⁣⁣

⁣⁣⁣
The coyote (Canis latrans) can be found from Alaska down through to Central America, and is a highly adaptable canine species. Certainly not a fussy eater, it will consume anything from medium-sized mammals to fruit and insects, dependent upon what it can find. ⁣

Although sometimes 'spotted' by day, these creatures are relatively nocturnal, and typically roost in tree holes or other cavities.⁣

Distinguishable features for fully matured individuals include its vibrant green plumage, black ring around its eyes, long blue tail and sharply pointed wings. ⁣

When you're the mane event 💅⁣
⁣
A lion's (Panthera leo) mane grows darker and more prominent with age. It can grow up to 16cm in length, and provides important information about the lion's health status and fighting ability. It is said that those who have a darker mane are more attractive to females, and more intimidating to potential rivals.⁣
